How to maintain your laptop battery<br/><br/>&lt;p&gt;People  who use the computers are more and more, and how to properly maintain your  laptop battery is also more and more concerned. In the following text I'll talk  about this aspect. &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.laptopaccessories.asia%2F%26quot%3B%26gt%3BLaptop"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.laptopaccessories.asia/&quot;&gt;Laptop</a>  Accessories&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt;A. Misunderstanding one: There is no need to charge the battery before  it is running out.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  Notebook  batteries are now lithium batteries. Lithium batteries, run out of battery  again for a long time filled with do not have any role, or even harmful.  Because lithium does not exist in the so-called &amp;quot;cache effect&amp;quot;, only  the early nickel batteries have this feature. Laptop battery life in general  with the man-made damage, or natural life. Basically, the battery life are  fixed 300-600 charge and discharge times, generally available 2 years.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  B.  Misunderstanding two: when the power is connected, the battery can pull or not  pull&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  &lt;br /&gt;
<br />  Pull or not pull depends on the actual usage: Connect the DC power at the same  time do not disconnect the battery and the battery does no harm, because the  battery is fully charged, will not accept any electricity into the power will  be directly to the laptop power supply supply system. But when the laptop  high-speed operation, the internal overheating is best to remove the battery,  otherwise it is harmful.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  C. How to  charge the laptop battery properly.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  We should  avoid the battery is run out of recharge, because this will give the battery a  lot of pressure which will resulting in damage. A more feasible approach is to  charge about 20-30% of power remaining. In fact the notebook lithium battery in  the number of &amp;quot;light / charge&amp;quot; is limited, all used to recharge will  significantly shorten the battery's life. At the same time, the battery should  be charged in a dry place, The heat problem, which also is the enemy of the  battery.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  Tip:  useing of mobile phone battery is different from that of laptop battery, many  people may experience in the use of mobile phone battery to determine that the  laptop battery should be all used up recharge, this idea is not true.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  D. How to protect the battery  which is not in use for a long time &lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;h1&gt;What should we do in protecting a  laptop battery, put photoelectric or  otherwise.  &lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.laptopaccessories.asia%2F%26quot%3B%26gt%3Blaptop"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.laptopaccessories.asia/&quot;&gt;laptop</a>  parts&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
<br />&lt;p&gt;Put the  photoelectric long-term preservation, the batteries will lose activity, and  even lead to the control circuit protection self-locking and can no longer use  fully charged, long-term preservation will bring safety risks, the best way to  save is the will power to about 40% and then stored in a cool, dry place, about  20 degrees Celsius is the ideal storage temperature. Of course, the best month  to take the battery out with time, can guarantee the battery good state of  preservation, but not so the battery is completely lost and damage the battery and  even lead to the control circuit protection self-locking and can no longer use  fully charged, long-term preservation will bring security risks, the best way  to save is the will power to about 40% and then stored in a cool, dry place,  about 20 degrees Celsius is the ideal storage temperature. Of course, the best  way to protect the battery is to take the battery out at least one month a  year, which can guarantee the battery's good state of preservation, and protecting  it from damage by completely lost.&lt;br /&gt;
<br />  E.  Several measures on extending laptop battery's working hours&lt;/p&gt;
<br />&lt;h1&gt;1&amp;gt; to  reduce the brightness of the screen: you can use the fn + down / up key  combination to quickly adjust brightness (specific the fn + which keys need to  see their own laptop).2&amp;gt; use of standby, sleep and other functions: when a  long time without a computer, notebook standby or hibernate, saving power and  extending the life of the computer.3&amp;gt; Open the cpu Speedstep function, can  greatly extend the battery working time: cpu speedstep function is the default  in the bios to start when using the battery, cpu will automatically drop the  frequency to use to save energy. If not open, you can boot into the BIOS, press  F2 to find the Performance settings Speedstep the Enable to Enabled.4&amp;gt; when  using the battery, try to turn off the wireless, Bluetooth and infrared port.  Removed without the use of peripherals and avoid enable large 3D applications,  games, etc., to reduce unnecessary battery consumption. &lt;a href=&quot;<a href="http://en.pan.netcom/go/out/url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.laptopaccessories.asia%2F%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bwww.laptopaccessories.asia%26lt%3B%2Fa%26gt%3B%26lt%3B%2Fh1%26gt"target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.laptopaccessories.asia/&quot;&gt;www.laptopaccessories.asia&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt</a>;

